  "local_port": 45322,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "My car back glass has been broken, how can I claim United India insurance?",
  "response": "If your car's back glass has been broken and you have a United India Insurance policy, you can follow these steps to file a claim:\n\n### 1. **Check Your Policy Details**\n   - Ensure that your car insurance policy covers \"glass breakage\" or \"own damage\" claims. Most comprehensive policies cover glass damage, but it's best to verify this in your policy document.\n\n### 2. **Inform the Insurance Company**\n   - **Immediately Report the Damage:** Contact United India Insurance as soon as possible to report the incident. You can do this via:\n     - **Customer Care:** Call their toll-free number (1800 425 1233 or 1800 209 5858).\n     - **Email:** Send an email to the claims department at customer.service@uiic.co.in.\n     - **Website:** Log in to their official website ([www.uiic.co.in](https://www.uiic.co.in)) and file the claim online.\n     - **Mobile App:** Use the United India Insurance mobile app to report the claim.\n\n### 3. **File the Claim**\n   - Provide the following details while filing the claim:\n     - Policy number\n     - Date and time of the incident\n     - Description of the damage (broken back glass)\n     - Any photos of the damage\n     - Details of the location where the incident occurred (if applicable)\n\n### 4. **Arrange for Inspection**\n   - The insurance company may send a surveyor to inspect the damage. Alternatively, they might ask you to visit a network garage for inspection.\n\n### 5. **Submit Required Documents**\n   - Be prepared to submit the following documents:\n     - Duly filled claim form (available on the website or app)\n     - Copy of the insurance policy\n     - RC copy of the vehicle\n     - Photos of the damaged glass\n     - Police FIR (if the damage was due to theft, vandalism, or an accident)\n     - Repair estimate from an authorized garage\n\n### 6. **Repair the Car**\n   - Once the claim is approved:\n     - Get your car repaired at an authorized garage or a United India Insurance network garage.\n     - If you\u2019ve already repaired the glass, submit the repair bills and payment receipts for reimbursement.\n\n### 7. **Claim Settlement**\n   - After submitting all documents and completing repairs, the insurance company will process your claim. Depending on the damage and policy terms, they may:\n     - Reimburse the repair cost directly.\n     - Settle the claim with the garage (in case of a cashless claim).\n\n### 8. **Follow Up**\n   - If there are any delays or issues, follow up with the insurance company by calling their customer care or contacting your insurance agent.\n\n### Tips:\n   - Keep all bills and documents safe for future reference.\n   - If the damage is minor and repair costs are less than the deductible (excess), it\u2019s better to avoid claiming insurance to maintain your No Claim Bonus (NCB).\n\nFor further assistance, you can visit the nearest United India Insurance branch or contact their customer support team.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
